---
---

<style>
  #about {
    padding: 100px 0;
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 60px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-text p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #9aa8bc;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .about-text p strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .about-text p em {
    color: var(--green);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .impact-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .impact-item {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--blue);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .impact-item:hover {
    border-left-color: var(--green);
  }

  .impact-item .num {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--blue);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .impact-item .desc {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .section-head {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .section-tag {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--green);
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .section-tag::before {
    content: '';
    width: 20px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--green);
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: 40px;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .section-title .accent {
    color: var(--blue);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    #about {
      padding: 72px 0;
    }

    .section-head {
      margin-bottom: 36px;
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 32px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .section-title {
      font-size: 28px;
    }
  }
</style>

<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-tag">About</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Who I <span class="accent">am.</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          Backend Engineer with <strong>+8 years</strong> building distributed systems and high-performance APIs in <strong>Go</strong>.
          I specialize in <em>event-driven architectures</em>, async processing with workers and queues, and production observability.
        </p>
        <p>
          I take <strong>full ownership</strong> of problems — from design to production.
          My track record includes rebuilding systems with critical design flaws, working directly with clients to arrive at the right solution.
          A key example: an authentication system rebuilt from scratch, now serving <em>70K+ users across 5 platforms with zero incidents post-launch</em>.
        </p>
        <p>
          I've built and technically led marketplace, fintech and SaaS platforms deployed on AWS and Azure over Kubernetes with CI/CD.
          I design solutions oriented around availability, latency and cost — and mentor teams to scale delivery without sacrificing quality.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="impact-list">
        <div class="impact-item">
          <div class="num">70K+</div>
          <div class="desc">Users served by Auth Manager — rebuilt from scratch with zero post-launch incidents</div>
        </div>
        <div class="impact-item">
          <div class="num">80%</div>
          <div class="desc">Response time improvement after migrating services to Go + FastAPI</div>
        </div>
        <div class="impact-item">
          <div class="num">62K+</div>
          <div class="desc">Records managed in Luxio (28K maintenance + 34K investigations) with background notifications</div>
        </div>
        <div class="impact-item">
          <div class="num">8K</div>
          <div class="desc">Registered users on NomadOS with ~2K active or historical memberships</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
